{"level":"info","message":"{\n  \"table\": \"FAQs Improvement With AI\",\n  \"sample\": [\n    {\n      \"AI_Question\": \"Which museum does this tour visit?\",\n      \"AI_Answer\": \"This tour takes you to the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization (NMEC) in Fustat, not the Egyptian Museum in Tahrir or the Grand Egyptian Museum. At NMEC you'll see the Royal Mummies Hall and over 50,000 artifacts.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"AI_Question\": \"What kind of food is served for lunch?\",\n      \"AI_Answer\": \"Lunch is an authentic Egyptian meal at a local restaurant. If you have dietary restrictions (e.g., vegetarian, gluten-free), you can request modifications when booking.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"AI_Question\": \"Is this tour suitable for children and elderly travelers?\",\n      \"AI_Answer\": \"Yes, the tour is generally suitable for all ages, but involves moderate walking. The vehicle is air-conditioned, and the pace is manageable. If you have specific mobility concerns, let us know at booking.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:28:16.288Z"}
