{"level":"info","message":"{\n  \"trip\": {\n    \"id\": \"recUDehvj1S32179Q\",\n    \"title\": \"Cairo: Egyptian Civilization Museum, Citadel &amp; Old Cairo Tour\",\n    \"tour_type\": \"\",\n    \"slug\": \"cairo-day-tour-nmec-citadel-old-cairo\",\n    \"duration_hours\": \"8\",\n    \"duration_minutes\": \"\",\n    \"duration_unit\": \"hours\"\n  },\n  \"seo\": {\n    \"title\": \"Cairo Day Tour: NMEC, Citadel & Old Cairo\",\n    \"meta_description\": \"Book this Cairo day tour to explore the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, Saladin's Citadel, and Old Cairo. Enjoy expert guidance and lunch.\",\n    \"excerpt\": \"Cairo day tour exploring the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, Saladin's Citadel, and Old Cairo. Includes expert guide, lunch, and hotel transfers.\",\n    \"focus_keywords\": \"Cairo day tour\",\n    \"permalink\": \"cairo-day-tour-nmec-citadel-old-cairo\"\n  },\n  \"evidence\": {\n    \"description\": \"Step into 5,000 years of Cairo's story in a single, seamless day. Begin at the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, where the Royal Mummies Hall brings pharaohs face-to-face with you. Then ascend Saladin's Citadel for panoramic views that stretch from medieval ramparts to the Pyramids on the horizon. Wander the narrow lanes of Old Cairo, step inside the Hanging Church suspended above a Roman fortress, and lose yourself in the spice-scented alleys of Khan El-Khalili Bazaar. Throughout, your expert Egyptologist guide connects each site with stories that make history come alive. This tour is perfect for first-time visitors who want a comprehensive, well-paced introduction to Cairo's layered heritage—from pharaonic and Coptic to Islamic eras. It may not suit travelers seeking deep dives into a single site or those with very limited mobility, as there is moderate walking at the Citadel and through Old Cairo's streets. Expect a comfortable, air-conditioned vehicle for all transfers, a relaxed pace with time for photos and shopping, and a traditional Egyptian lunch to refuel. Bring comfortable walking shoes, a hat, sunscreen, and cash for personal purchases or tips.\",\n    \"why_people_love\": \"Expert Storytelling — Your Egyptologist guide doesn't just point out artifacts; they reveal the stories behind royal mummies, fortress walls, and Coptic icons, making every stop unforgettable. Seamless Logistics — Hotel pickup and drop-off in a guided air-conditioned vehicle eliminate traffic stress, so you focus on the sights, not the commute. All-Inclusive Value — Entrance fees, lunch, and bottled water are all covered—no surprise costs, just a full day of discovery. Unique Blend of Eras — See pharaonic, medieval Islamic, and Coptic Christian heritage in one tour, a combination most Cairo tours miss. Perfect for First-Timers — Covers the must-see sights (NMEC, Citadel, Old Cairo, Khan El-Khalili) at a comfortable pace, ideal for history buffs, families, and solo travelers. Memorable Views — Standing atop the Citadel with the Pyramids on the horizon or gazing at royal mummies creates lasting emotional payoffs you'll talk about for years.\",\n    \"highlights\": \"Stand atop Saladin's 850-year-old Citadel for panoramic Cairo views and a strategic history lesson from your guide. | Trace 5,000 years of civilization at NMEC—from pharaonic mummies to Coptic icons—all in one museum. | Step inside the Hanging Church's wooden nave, suspended above a Roman fortress in Old Cairo. | Savor a traditional Egyptian lunch with authentic flavors that connect you to Cairo's culinary heritage. | Haggle for treasures at Khan El-Khalili Bazaar, a 14th-century market alive with spices, lanterns, and jewelry.\",\n    \"itinerary\": \"Morning (30 minutes) – Hotel Pickup & Transfer to NMEC: Your guide picks you up from your Cairo or Giza hotel in an air-conditioned vehicle and briefs you on the day ahead. This stress-free start ensures you arrive ready to explore. (Approx. 30 minutes) | Morning (2 hours) – National Museum of Egyptian Civilization: Explore NMEC's 50,000 artifacts, including the Royal Mummies Hall, where you'll see the preserved faces of pharaohs. This immersive journey through Egypt's past is a highlight of any Cairo sightseeing adventure. (Approx. 2 hours) | Late Morning (30 minutes) – Transfer to Saladin's Citadel: Drive through Cairo's vibrant streets as your guide shares stories of the city's evolution from ancient times to the medieval era. The short ride builds anticipation for the panoramic views ahead. (Approx. 30 minutes) | Late Morning (1 hour) – Saladin's Citadel & City Views: Explore the 850-year-old fortress that once protected Cairo from crusaders, then soak in 360-degree views with the Pyramids on the horizon. This stop offers a perfect blend of history and photography opportunities. (Approx. 1 hours) | Lunch (1 hour) – Traditional Egyptian Meal: Savor a delicious traditional Egyptian lunch at a local restaurant, featuring dishes like koshari, grilled meats, and fresh salads. This midday break recharges you for the afternoon's discoveries. (Approx. 1 hours) | Afternoon (30 minutes) – Transfer to Old Cairo: Head south to the historic district of Old Cairo, where Coptic churches and Roman ruins line narrow lanes. Your guide points out landmarks along the way, weaving together stories of faith and resilience. (Approx. 30 minutes) | Afternoon (1 hour) – Old Cairo & The Hanging Church: Wander through ancient streets and visit the Hanging Church, one of the oldest Coptic Christian sites in Egypt, with its wooden roof suspended over a Roman fortress. This serene stop reveals a side of Cairo that many visitors miss. (Approx. 1 hours) | Late Afternoon (1 hour) – Khan El-Khalili Bazaar: Lose yourself in the labyrinthine alleys of Cairo's most famous bazaar since the 14th century, browsing stalls of spices, lanterns, jewelry, and handcrafted souvenirs. This is the perfect place to haggle for unique treasures and soak in the lively atmosphere. (Approx. 1 hours) | Late Afternoon (30 minutes) – Return Transfer to Hotel: Your tour concludes with a comfortable drop-off at your hotel, giving you time to relax and reflect on a day filled with ancient mummies, medieval fortresses, and bustling markets. You'll return with a deeper understanding of Cairo's layered history. (Approx. 30 minutes)\",\n    \"included\": \"Entrance fees to the Hanging Church and Old Cairo sites | Visit to Khan El-Khalili Bazaar (if time permits) | Entrance fees to the Citadel of Saladin | Expert English-speaking Egyptologist guide for captivating storytelling | Entrance fees to the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization (NMEC) | Bottled water throughout the tour | Air-conditioned transportation with hotel pickup and drop-off in Cairo or Giza | Traditional Egyptian lunch at a local restaurant\",\n    \"excluded\": \"Personal expenses and shopping | Gratuities and tips | Travel insurance | Any items not mentioned in the inclusions\",\n    \"faqs\": \"What is included in the tour price? — Please refer to the 'What's Included' and 'What's included' sections on this page for a detailed list. Entrance-fee coverage and guiding depend on the option selected. | Which museum does this tour visit? — This tour takes you to the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization (NMEC) in Fustat, not the older Egyptian Museum in Tahrir or the Grand Egyptian Museum. At NMEC, you’ll see over 50,000 artifacts and the Royal Mummies Hall. | Is this tour suitable for children or elderly travelers? — Yes, the tour is generally suitable for all ages, but it involves walking at the Citadel and through Old Cairo’s narrow streets. The NMEC is wheelchair-accessible, and the vehicle is air-conditioned. Let us know about any mobility needs at booking so we can assist. | Where does the tour start and end? — The tour begins with a hotel pickup from your Cairo accommodation and ends with a drop-off at your hotel. The exact pickup time is confirmed after booking—just provide your hotel details when you reserve. | What food is included, and can dietary restrictions be accommodated? — Yes. Lunch is included as listed in What's Included. | What are the main stops on this tour? — Your Cairo day tour includes the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization (NMEC), Saladin’s Citadel with panoramic city views, Old Cairo’s Hanging Church, and Khan El-Khalili Bazaar. Lunch at a local restaurant is also part of the itinerary. | What should I bring on this Cairo day tour? — Bring comfortable walking shoes, a hat, sunscreen, and a camera for the Citadel views and museum exhibits. Carry some cash in Egyptian pounds for personal purchases at Khan El-Khalili bazaar, tips, or any optional extras included in your booking. | Can I customize the itinerary or skip a stop? — This is a fixed Cairo day tour designed to cover the highlights efficiently, but your guide can adjust the pace. If you need to skip a stop due to time or interest, just let your guide know. | What languages are available for the guided tour? — Language availability is confirmed at booking. Please specify your preferred language when reserving. | What is the cancellation policy? — You’ll receive a full refund if you cancel at least 24 hours before the scheduled trip. Use the booking details provided after confirmation to cancel or reschedule.\",\n    \"packages\": \"Egyptian Civilization Museum, Citadel &#038; Old Cairo Tour — Experience 5,000 years of Cairo's history in one perfect day. Includes expert guide, all entrance fees, lunch, and hotel transfers. — Your all-inclusive Cairo day tour includes: Expert Egyptologist guide bringing history to life with captivating storytelling All attraction entrance fees for seamless access to every site Comfortable air-conditioned transportation with hotel pickup and drop-off Traditional Egyptian lunch at a local restaurant with authentic cuisine Bottled water throughout to keep you refreshed | Egyptian Museum, Citadel, and Old Cairo Guided Tour | GetYourGuide | Egyptian Museum, Citadel, and Old Cairo Guided Tour | GetYourGuide\",\n    \"combined\": \"Cairo: Egyptian Civilization Museum, Citadel &amp; Old Cairo Tour | Cairo Day Tour: NMEC, Citadel & Old Cairo | Book this Cairo day tour to explore the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, Saladin's Citadel, and Old Cairo. Enjoy expert guidance and lunch. | Cairo day tour exploring the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, Saladin's Citadel, and Old Cairo. Includes expert guide, lunch, and hotel transfers. | Step into 5,000 years of Cairo's story in a single, seamless day. Begin at the National Museum of Egyptian Civilization, where the Royal Mummies Hall brings pharaohs face-to-face with you. Then ascend Saladin's Citadel for panoramic views that stretch from medieval ramparts to the Pyramids on the horizon. Wander the narrow lanes of Old Cairo, step inside the Hanging Church suspended above a Roman fortress, and lose yourself in the spice-scented alleys of Khan El-Khalili Bazaar. Throughout, your expert Egyptologist guide connects each site with stories that make history come alive. This tour is perfect for first-time visitors who want a comprehensive, well-paced introduction to Cairo's layered heritage—from pharaonic and Coptic to Islamic eras. It may not suit travelers seeking deep dives into a single site or those with very limited mobility, as there is moderate walking at the Citadel and through Old Cairo's streets. Expect a comfortable, air-conditioned vehicle for all transfers, a relaxed pace with time for photos and shopping, and a traditional Egyptian lunch to refuel. Bring comfortable walking shoes, a hat, sunscreen, and cash for personal purchases or tips. | Expert Storytelling — Your Egyptologist guide doesn't just point out artifacts; they reveal the stories behind royal mummies, fortress walls, and Coptic icons, making every stop unforgettable. Seamless Logistics — Hotel pickup and drop-off in a guided air-conditioned vehicle eliminate traffic stress, so you focus on 